<br>
-------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
1. Guilds may hold a total of two spots, one on each of two out of the three lists.<br>
2. Guild spots are owned by the guild. If the person listed leaves his/her guild the guild retains the spot.<br>
4. If the guild disbands the spot on the rotation will be deleted.<br>
5. Each Independent Raid Organizer may hold one spot total on any of the three lists. That IRO may not transfer spots to anyone. As an IRO you are making a commitment of yourself to host that raid. <br>
6. If an IRO holds a spot and joins a guild that currently holds the maximum spots listed in rule 2 the IRO loses his/her spot without compensation. If adding the spot to the guild does not violate rule 2 then the guild name is added to the spot.<br>
7. To be added to a list you post your request in the forum specific to that list.<br>
8. Once a raid is completed then you must request to be placed back on a list. You will not be added automatically.<br>
9. You may not sign up using an alternate character or friend to give you multiple spots. This one will need to be enforced by the honor system and the general population calling the ones that try to get around it.<br>
10. If this is accepted all current lists are kept, as is, with the exception of those holding multiple spots that violate #2 &amp; #3. For those that have more spots than allowed they must choose which spots they will give up to be within compliance.<br>
<br>
<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
<br>
1. Raid leaders MUST report the exact time (within a few minutes) of the death of that particular ubermob to Zest so that spawn time will be known.<br>
2. All people on the list are responsible to check the thread often when they are in the top few spots as they may be up a few spots early based on others passing or server outages spawning the mobs early.<br>
3. Your turn starts at 12:01 AM Board time following spawning or 12:01 AM Board time following a previously failed raid's slot.<br>
4. You have 48 hours from the start of your turn to take the mob down or lose your spot.<br>
5. You may make as many attempts as you wish during that 48 hour period. Once that 48 hour period is up it goes to the next person in line and you are removed from the list.<br>
6. You must post your intention to either procede with an attempt or pass no later than 48 hours BEFORE the expected spawn time listed in the list thread. <br>
7. The person/guild &quot;on-deck&quot; must prepare to have a raid during the 48 hours immediately following the current raids 48 hours in case of a failed raid.<br>
<br>
<br>
Exceptions to these rules because of server resets will be as follows.<br>
<br>
1. For unannounced server outages/zone resets: If a mob is respawned early due to server resets, the person has 24 hours from the reset to post their intents to either attempt or pass. . If you intend to make an attempt you have 72 hours after the servers come back online to make your attempt. <br>
2. For unannounced server outages/zone crashes during the raid will extend the time allowed from 48 hours to 72 hours.<br>
3. For scheduled/announced server outages less than 48 hours in advance you have 24 hours from the time of the announcement to state your intents. If you intend to make an attempt you have 48 hours after the servers come back online to make your attempt. <br>
4. For scheduled/announced server outages over 48 hours in advance you have till 48 hours (or a minimum of 24 hours from the announcement) before the expected outage to state your intents. If you intend to make an attempt you have 48 hours after the servers come back online to make your attempt. <br>
<br>
<br>
If you fail to post your intentions within the specified time limits then you will be moved to the bottom of the list. Please notify Selilya or Kestri if you are going to pass and you will be moved to the bottom of the list.<br>
